<p>GDP growth: 4.0% GDP: $182bn (PPP: $335bn) Inflation: 3.9% Population: 37.1m GDP per head: $4,910 (PPP: $9,020)</p>

<p>Bordering two countries whose regimes were booted out in the Arab spring, Algeria's leaders will try to avoid the same fate. The three-term president, Abdelaziz Bouteflika, has made concessions and more are under review, but none that will threaten the military elite. Parliamentary elections in 2012 will see some shifts in party politics, but only in the context of the battle to succeed Mr Bouteflika when his term ends in 2014.</p>

<p>To watch: ‘allo ‘allo. A nationwide third-generation mobile-phone network will be launched in 2012, following the auction of licences by the government the year before. </p>

